File: ocp-ipi-powervc/VMs.go
Line: 96 to 111
Type: potential_issue
Severity: major

Comment:
innerNewVMs returns a pre-allocated error slice with a nil entry, which misleads callers.

errs = make([]error, 1) produces []error{nil} — a non-empty slice where the sole element is nil. Any caller that gates on len(errs) == 0 or errs != nil to detect a clean construction will incorrectly interpret this as an error condition. The idiomatic Go convention is to return nil (or nothing) when there are no errors.




🐛 Proposed fix

 func innerNewVMs(services Services) ([]VMs, []error) {
-	var (
-		vms  []*VMs
-		errs []error
-	)
-
